WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.690 --> 00:00:05.655
Brothers and sisters, today's
passage from the Holy Scripture

00:00:05.655 --> 00:00:09.518
is quite familiar to all of us.

00:00:09.518 --> 00:00:15.036
It talks about two men,
a rich man and Lazarus.

00:00:15.036 --> 00:00:22.209
Lazarus is poor, begging every
day to be fed with the crumbs that

00:00:22.209 --> 00:00:25.519
fall from the rich man's table.

00:00:25.519 --> 00:00:33.796
The first thing we need to notice is
that it's rare for the Holy Scripture

00:00:33.796 --> 00:00:36.555
to mention someone's personal name.

00:00:37.535 --> 00:00:40.297
Here it mentions the name Lazarus.

00:00:40.297 --> 00:00:46.283
We don't know who the rich man
is, but we know Lazarus's name.

00:00:46.283 --> 00:00:52.269
So, if in the Holy Scripture Jesus
highlighted the name Lazarus, it means

00:00:52.269 --> 00:00:58.715
that God cares so much about him that
He mentions him personally by name.

00:00:58.715 --> 00:01:04.241
How often do we forget that
we received a name at baptism?

00:01:04.241 --> 00:01:10.227
And in the Holy Scripture, it
says in one place, I have called

00:01:10.227 --> 00:01:12.990
you by name, you are mine.

00:01:13.790 --> 00:01:16.714
Well, you know, it continues further.

00:01:16.714 --> 00:01:24.026
Each of us has a name, and God
knows us just as He knows Lazarus.

00:01:24.026 --> 00:01:31.337
But here, He wants to emphasize even more
the closeness to Lazarus, because he is

00:01:31.337 --> 00:01:34.749
the one who begs and literally survives.

00:01:34.749 --> 00:01:39.624
He is by the rich man's
table, feeding on crumbs.

00:01:39.624 --> 00:01:45.960
You have to understand that at that
time, the description of this rich

00:01:45.960 --> 00:01:51.810
man says that he enjoyed feasting
every day and wore expensive clothes.

00:01:53.160 --> 00:01:58.516
So, in their culture at that time,
when something greasy was eaten,

00:01:58.516 --> 00:02:01.194
hands would be cleaned with bread.

00:02:01.194 --> 00:02:07.889
And then that bread would be thrown
under the table for the dogs to eat.

00:02:07.889 --> 00:02:13.245
And this poor Lazar only wanted
to live off that bread, those

00:02:13.245 --> 00:02:15.923
crumbs that even the dogs ate.

00:02:15.923 --> 00:02:21.280
Now, the first thing I want
everyone to notice tonight is this.

00:02:22.835 --> 00:02:29.589
So it says here that it wasn't just
once, Lazar constantly comes to his door.

00:02:29.589 --> 00:02:31.390
He's always there, waiting.

00:02:31.390 --> 00:02:33.191
What would you think?

00:02:33.191 --> 00:02:39.945
You come to a church once, beg, no
one gives you anything, you come a

00:02:39.945 --> 00:02:45.798
second time, you'd probably be tempted
to say, "I'll go to another church,

00:02:45.798 --> 00:02:50.751
maybe they're more generous." It's very
interesting that Lazar is persistent.

00:02:50.751 --> 00:02:55.704
He doesn't change location, he
doesn't go knocking on other doors.

00:02:56.255 --> 00:03:04.362
He persistently stands there, and probably
every day when he comes, he thinks maybe

00:03:04.362 --> 00:03:08.416
this rich man will change his mind.

00:03:08.416 --> 00:03:15.366
Now, on the other hand, imagine how
many opportunities this rich man

00:03:15.366 --> 00:03:18.841
missed to feed this poor Lazarus.

00:03:18.841 --> 00:03:25.791
And now we can immediately see an
interesting fact, which is that

00:03:25.791 --> 00:03:29.845
this rich man still had his role.

00:03:29.864 --> 00:03:35.197
God blessed him well, in Jewish
times wealth and prosperity

00:03:35.197 --> 00:03:37.330
were considered God's blessing.

00:03:37.330 --> 00:03:40.530
But, God gives him a mission.

00:03:40.530 --> 00:03:47.996
This passage of the Gospel does not
describe anywhere that this rich man ended

00:03:47.996 --> 00:03:52.262
up in hell because of some other sin.

00:03:52.262 --> 00:03:59.195
It doesn't say he killed anyone,
it doesn't say he was a fornicator,

00:03:59.195 --> 00:04:05.595
it doesn't say he deceived or
stole from anyone, no other sin.

00:04:05.734 --> 00:04:10.048
And he ends up in the torments of hell.

00:04:10.048 --> 00:04:11.007
How come?

00:04:11.007 --> 00:04:18.197
You see, God blessed him to be rich,
but He also gave him a mission.

00:04:18.197 --> 00:04:22.511
And his mission was to
feed the hungry Lazarus.

00:04:22.511 --> 00:04:27.783
Now imagine how many times that
rich man missed the opportunity

00:04:27.783 --> 00:04:34.493
right at his doorstep to make that
poor Lazarus happy and to feed him.

00:04:34.493 --> 00:04:40.725
And when we see why he ended
up in the torments of hell.

00:04:41.610 --> 00:04:44.815
If not, no other sins are mentioned.

00:04:44.815 --> 00:04:49.851
So he ended up there because
of the sin of omission.

00:04:49.851 --> 00:04:54.888
This means that each of us,
dear believers, has a mission.

00:04:54.888 --> 00:05:02.214
Lazar was given the mission to perform an
act of love by feeding this poor Lazarus.

00:05:02.214 --> 00:05:09.540
So, this is about the sin of omission,
the sin of love, and the sin of

00:05:09.540 --> 00:05:11.830
mercy because he lacked compassion.

00:05:12.430 --> 00:05:18.424
So maybe he, when you look at it
realistically, maybe he didn't notice.

00:05:18.424 --> 00:05:23.957
Maybe it wasn't intentional malice
that he didn't want to feed him.

00:05:23.957 --> 00:05:26.262
But still, he didn't notice.

00:05:26.262 --> 00:05:29.490
He didn't have a sense for him.

00:05:29.490 --> 00:05:31.795
What about us, dear believers?

00:05:31.795 --> 00:05:37.790
Do we always have a sense of
the mission we are chosen for?

00:05:37.790 --> 00:05:41.940
Do we know exactly what we need to do?

00:05:43.120 --> 00:05:49.516
Maybe some Lazarus, or a female Lazarus,
stands next to us every day as well.

00:05:49.516 --> 00:05:51.648
And maybe we don't notice.

00:05:51.648 --> 00:05:58.044
Let's be clear when we listen to
this, none of us here is overly rich.

00:05:58.044 --> 00:06:02.735
And to suddenly dismiss it and
say, look, this gospel today

00:06:02.735 --> 00:06:05.293
doesn't concern me, I'm not rich.

00:06:05.293 --> 00:06:11.690
No one here, I believe, has never made
a gesture of love towards someone poor.

00:06:12.380 --> 00:06:18.319
Surely, you have helped someone,
given alms, volunteered, you have

00:06:18.319 --> 00:06:21.288
certainly done something for someone.

00:06:21.288 --> 00:06:28.415
But we cannot be immune to
those Lazars who are beside us.

00:06:28.415 --> 00:06:31.979
We admire, we highlight great examples.

00:06:31.979 --> 00:06:40.887
We will say, look, when we talk about
war, we will say, look, this soldier

00:06:40.887 --> 00:06:45.044
gave his life, fought for five years.

00:06:45.424 --> 00:06:48.155
We appreciate that, we respect it.

00:06:48.155 --> 00:06:54.069
When we hear about a missionary
in Africa for 20, 15 years, we'll

00:06:54.069 --> 00:06:59.530
say, wow, hats off, I couldn't
do it, truly a great project.

00:06:59.530 --> 00:07:05.445
And so many times we see and admire
those big projects, those grand

00:07:05.445 --> 00:07:07.265
gestures that individuals undertake.

00:07:07.265 --> 00:07:13.179
Today, we all watched on TV the
scene of those astronauts who were

00:07:13.179 --> 00:07:19.094
lost in space for two hundred and
something days and have now returned

00:07:19.094 --> 00:07:21.825
to Earth, truly a great thing.

00:07:22.225 --> 00:07:29.982
A great sacrifice, they surely researched
for the betterment of humanity and so on.

00:07:29.982 --> 00:07:35.524
And then we disconnect and
say, okay, we admire big

00:07:35.524 --> 00:07:38.848
projects, but that's not for me.

00:07:38.848 --> 00:07:43.835
But does God call us to do similar things?

00:07:43.835 --> 00:07:49.377
Does God call us to do
only those big things?

00:07:49.377 --> 00:07:49.931
No.

00:07:49.931 --> 00:07:57.135
God calls us, through this Gospel
today, to do small and simple things.

00:07:58.915 --> 00:08:01.041
Let's start with our social life.

00:08:01.041 --> 00:08:06.004
Just think, you go to handle some
documents and you come across a kind

00:08:06.004 --> 00:08:10.967
woman working there who has love and
guides you to the right address, and

00:08:10.967 --> 00:08:14.867
doesn't just dismiss you saying you're
missing this document, but nicely

00:08:14.867 --> 00:08:17.348
explains what exactly you need to do.

00:08:17.348 --> 00:08:22.311
Imagine you young people when you see
an elderly person on the tram, you

00:08:22.311 --> 00:08:27.274
get up and say, please sit, instead of
putting on your headphones and tuning

00:08:27.274 --> 00:08:31.883
out, looking outside and pretending
not to notice a pregnant woman or a

00:08:31.883 --> 00:08:34.010
sick grandmother standing next to you.

00:08:36.160 --> 00:08:40.176
You see, those are the
little Lazaruses around us.

00:08:40.176 --> 00:08:45.977
There are many things we could do
for our society and feed people.

00:08:45.977 --> 00:08:52.225
All these people around us, we
aren't even aware of it, even in this

00:08:52.225 --> 00:08:55.349
church, they are all people in need.

00:08:55.349 --> 00:08:59.812
They don't need anyone
else to come to their aid.

00:08:59.812 --> 00:09:05.613
Maybe, just like the rich man,
God placed you where you are to

00:09:05.613 --> 00:09:07.845
fulfill a mission through you.

00:09:08.645 --> 00:09:14.142
Lazar did not fulfill his mission
because he closed himself off, because

00:09:14.142 --> 00:09:20.099
he persistently ignored and did not
notice the poor man at his doorstep.

00:09:20.099 --> 00:09:26.055
We don't have to dream of grand
projects; let's look at our own

00:09:26.055 --> 00:09:29.262
doorstep, at the people close to us.

00:09:29.262 --> 00:09:31.095
Do we notice them?

00:09:31.095 --> 00:09:37.967
I just said that Lazar committed the
sin of omission for so many years, and

00:09:37.967 --> 00:09:44.840
this poor man, so persistent, was not
noticed at his doorstep, a man in need.

00:09:48.425 --> 00:09:55.013
We can all regularly perform small
acts of love for those who beg,

00:09:55.013 --> 00:10:01.094
who beg for our attention, who
beg for our love, for support,

00:10:01.094 --> 00:10:03.121
for friendship, for encouragement.

00:10:03.121 --> 00:10:08.189
But do we notice if we
have lost that sense?

00:10:08.189 --> 00:10:15.284
The sense of mission that God has placed
us to bring encouragement to someone.

00:10:15.284 --> 00:10:22.379
These are the everyday crumbs that
we can all give to others, and we

00:10:22.379 --> 00:10:25.420
don't have to be explicitly wealthy.

00:10:26.030 --> 00:10:32.196
We don't need to possess extraordinary
things to fulfill God's mission.

00:10:32.196 --> 00:10:36.120
What about the crumbs in our families?

00:10:40.250 --> 00:10:45.617
Sometimes, when I hear about the
situations in our families, it's sad.

00:10:45.617 --> 00:10:50.538
Imagine if in families everyone
fed each other crumbs of love.

00:10:50.538 --> 00:10:53.670
What kind of atmosphere would that create?

00:10:56.780 --> 00:11:02.260
Imagine if a husband came to his wife's
aid, washed the dishes, or helped with

00:11:02.260 --> 00:11:07.010
something else, and the wife did the
same for her husband, and children

00:11:07.010 --> 00:11:09.568
showed gestures of love to their parents.

00:11:09.568 --> 00:11:13.587
Imagine having grandparents in the
family, and you give grandpa his

00:11:13.587 --> 00:11:18.337
slippers so he can walk, and you
listen to grandma repeating her old

00:11:18.337 --> 00:11:23.452
stories, the same story over and
over, and you have a bit of patience

00:11:23.452 --> 00:11:26.010
to listen to that same story again.

00:11:26.330 --> 00:11:31.214
Imagine what the state of
our families would be like.

00:11:31.214 --> 00:11:38.053
We make so many mistakes, much bigger
than this rich man, much bigger, because

00:11:38.053 --> 00:11:45.869
we, like him, have turned a deaf ear to
doing good, as if we've been vaccinated

00:11:45.869 --> 00:11:48.800
against love to make others happy.

00:11:48.800 --> 00:11:56.616
And we all know that we will never be
happy while we are focused on ourselves.

00:11:56.616 --> 00:12:04.920
Okay, Lazar ended up in torment because
of it, but maybe you and I will also end

00:12:04.920 --> 00:12:12.736
up in some kind of suffering because we
didn't show love to our spouse, our child,

00:12:12.736 --> 00:12:19.575
or a wife to her husband, or children
to their parents, friends to friends.

00:12:19.755 --> 00:12:24.296
So, we all sit close to someone and yearn.

00:12:24.296 --> 00:12:28.332
You can imagine what that meant for Lazar.

00:12:28.332 --> 00:12:28.837
Crumbs.

00:12:28.837 --> 00:12:31.864
For him, it was literally survival.

00:12:31.864 --> 00:12:32.369
Survival.

00:12:32.369 --> 00:12:38.423
How many people do I see today who are
spiritually, psychologically, emotionally.

00:12:38.423 --> 00:12:40.946
Emotionally, people are barely surviving.

00:12:40.946 --> 00:12:48.515
Because who knows when was the last time
someone gave them a word of support.

00:12:48.600 --> 00:12:55.568
Kind words, I love you, I believe
in you, I'll help you, I'm with you,

00:12:55.568 --> 00:12:58.356
don't be afraid, let's go together.

00:12:58.356 --> 00:13:04.860
These are words that have vanished from
our vocabulary, from our way of life.

00:13:04.860 --> 00:13:09.506
Especially, I repeat and return
to our family, our environment.

00:13:09.506 --> 00:13:15.546
This Lazarus wasn't far from the
rich man, he was at his feet.

00:13:15.546 --> 00:13:19.727
Let's all think tonight
about why we might suffer.

00:13:19.727 --> 00:13:27.161
If we hold back from doing good and
loving, and we all do that a bit,

00:13:27.161 --> 00:13:33.200
how can a married couple start off
idyllically and then over time that

00:13:33.200 --> 00:13:37.846
marriage becomes hell, simply emotional
exhaustion, fatigue, lack of love,

00:13:37.846 --> 00:13:42.028
many friendships, many relationships
because we simply lose ourselves

00:13:42.028 --> 00:13:45.745
and don't notice the one next to us.

00:13:46.285 --> 00:13:52.285
Whoever prays, notice me, I am alive, I
am a person, I am a woman, I am a man,

00:13:52.285 --> 00:13:56.706
say something nice to me, do something
for me, because that is your mission.

00:13:56.706 --> 00:14:00.812
If you have chosen the mission
to be a husband, be a husband.

00:14:00.812 --> 00:14:05.233
If you have chosen the mission
to be a wife and mother, be that.

00:14:05.233 --> 00:14:08.392
If you have chosen to
be a priest, be that.

00:14:08.392 --> 00:14:10.918
Friend, girlfriend, how many
false friendships are there

00:14:10.918 --> 00:14:12.497
today, everyone lies to us.

00:14:12.497 --> 00:14:15.340
When I say they lie,
it's the living truth.

00:14:15.340 --> 00:14:17.522
Why do I claim this?

00:14:17.522 --> 00:14:21.015
Dear young people, dear
believers, we shouldn't ask

00:14:21.015 --> 00:14:23.634
someone what we mean to them.

00:14:23.634 --> 00:14:25.380
That's a silly question.

00:14:25.380 --> 00:14:32.802
If you have to ask someone to tell you
what you mean to them, let your gestures,

00:14:32.802 --> 00:14:34.985
your behavior answer that question.

00:14:34.985 --> 00:14:40.223
When we show such gestures, such
love towards others, there's no need

00:14:40.223 --> 00:14:47.208
to ask what we mean to them, as a
friend, as a neighbor, as a relative,

00:14:47.208 --> 00:14:48.955
brother, sister, mother, father.

00:14:48.955 --> 00:14:56.490
I will show you with a gesture, I
don't need to ask what I mean to you.

00:14:56.490 --> 00:15:00.923
Let actions speak, let words
be silent, said Saint Anthony.

00:15:00.923 --> 00:15:02.696
That's what we need.

00:15:02.696 --> 00:15:07.129
And how many are there
around us who are begging?

00:15:07.129 --> 00:15:10.675
Those we don't see, those we don't notice.

00:15:10.675 --> 00:15:13.335
Maybe the rich man wasn't malicious.

00:15:13.335 --> 00:15:16.438
He simply committed the sin of omission.

00:15:16.438 --> 00:15:18.655
We do it every day.

00:15:18.655 --> 00:15:21.163
I'm the first because I don't have time.

00:15:21.163 --> 00:15:26.179
I don't have time to dedicate to friends,
I don't have time for family, I don't

00:15:26.179 --> 00:15:30.882
have time for this, I don't have time
for that, but we're all like that.

00:15:30.882 --> 00:15:32.136
We need to stop.

00:15:32.136 --> 00:15:34.958
We need to think about
what's important to us.

00:15:34.958 --> 00:15:36.839
What will send us to heaven?

00:15:39.959 --> 00:15:42.439
The rich man ended up in torment, why?

00:15:46.420 --> 00:15:49.085
Due to a lack of love.

00:15:49.085 --> 00:15:55.306
So, God will judge us based on
how we lived and what we did.

00:15:55.306 --> 00:16:01.082
Remember Golgotha, and the thief on
the right who repented at the last

00:16:01.082 --> 00:16:07.303
moment, but he repented with love and
cried out and ended up in paradise.

00:16:07.303 --> 00:16:13.079
Nowhere will God ask us, when we
come before Him, about our big

00:16:13.079 --> 00:16:17.522
projects, about some recognitions
we received from society, from the

00:16:17.522 --> 00:16:22.410
president, or even the pope giving some
acknowledgments to active believers.

00:16:22.410 --> 00:16:25.491
God won't ask you that either.

00:16:25.491 --> 00:16:33.194
He will ask you about those you loved,
whose pain, thirst, and hunger you eased.

00:16:33.194 --> 00:16:34.735
That is Lent.

00:16:34.735 --> 00:16:36.276
That is life.

00:16:36.276 --> 00:16:42.438
So, brothers and sisters, may
the Lord grant us the grace to

00:16:42.438 --> 00:16:46.033
recognize in time those who need us.

00:16:46.033 --> 00:16:49.628
We constantly think about what we need.

00:16:49.628 --> 00:16:52.710
We constantly check who loves us.

00:16:53.250 --> 00:16:57.777
We are always looking at who
will do something for us.

00:16:57.777 --> 00:17:00.659
But... God's economy
doesn't work that way.

00:17:00.659 --> 00:17:05.186
God's economy works the more
you love, the more you receive.

00:17:05.186 --> 00:17:12.184
As I said before, you never need to ask
anyone how much you mean to them, let

00:17:12.184 --> 00:17:14.654
them show you through their actions.

00:17:14.654 --> 00:17:17.947
Is it really that hard to call someone?

00:17:17.947 --> 00:17:21.240
Is it really that hard
to encourage someone?

00:17:21.579 --> 00:17:27.533
In the end, is it really
that hard to say I love you?

00:17:27.533 --> 00:17:29.823
Forgive me, I'm only human.

00:17:29.823 --> 00:17:37.151
And we have a feeling that we live in
a time when we've stopped being human.

00:17:37.151 --> 00:17:40.814
We often talk about faith
and spirituality, but

00:17:40.814 --> 00:17:43.104
above all, let's be human.

00:17:43.104 --> 00:17:47.226
Jesus gives us the commandment
to love one another.

00:17:47.226 --> 00:17:53.180
We cannot love God so much without
seeing a brother or sister in

00:17:53.180 --> 00:17:55.470
need and loving them first.

00:17:58.649 --> 00:18:03.034
Many of us might be suffering
greatly because of this.

00:18:03.034 --> 00:18:08.735
And we're all waiting, right, for
that day when they'll say we're good.

00:18:08.735 --> 00:18:13.558
Well, the day when everyone says
you're good, that you're the

00:18:13.558 --> 00:18:16.189
best, that day you're surely dead.

00:18:19.070 --> 00:18:23.335
And Lazarus ended up, and the
Rich Man ended up in torment.

00:18:23.335 --> 00:18:26.889
Maybe they also spoke
well of him when he died.

00:18:26.889 --> 00:18:31.865
The plan is not for people to
say we were good when we die.

00:18:32.205 --> 00:18:40.065
They speak praises, as they say,
always the best about the deceased.

00:18:40.065 --> 00:18:45.304
But we need to ask
ourselves this question.

00:18:45.304 --> 00:18:47.925
One woman said that

00:18:51.095 --> 00:18:54.085
someone told her she looked sad.

00:18:54.085 --> 00:19:00.065
And she replied, I am sad
every day, I just didn't have

00:19:00.065 --> 00:19:03.055
the strength to hide it today.

00:19:06.555 --> 00:19:13.807
And as a priest, I encounter so many
people who are sad, who perhaps no longer

00:19:13.807 --> 00:19:16.980
have the strength to hide their condition.

00:19:16.980 --> 00:19:23.778
That's why I'm telling you it's
good to open our eyes to who is the

00:19:23.778 --> 00:19:27.405
Lazarus at our feet, whom we can help.

00:19:32.565 --> 00:19:38.645
Now, this might sound a bit funny
to say, but it's true because

00:19:38.645 --> 00:19:44.258
sometimes I have trouble sleeping,
and then someone tells you to rest,

00:19:44.258 --> 00:19:47.065
saying, "Well, go get some sleep."

00:19:52.015 --> 00:19:57.832
But there is a kind of fatigue
that sleep cannot cure.

00:19:57.832 --> 00:20:03.649
Sometimes, no bed or dreams can
reset you after you've slept.

00:20:03.649 --> 00:20:09.995
Because sometimes it's not physical
exhaustion but a pain in your soul.

00:20:09.995 --> 00:20:16.869
When your soul hurts, as it does
for many people, not even dreams

00:20:16.869 --> 00:20:21.100
can help, but a gesture of love can.

00:20:21.100 --> 00:20:27.975
So, we all live off small, nameless
acts of love, off small gestures.

00:20:28.695 --> 00:20:33.260
Lazar lived off small crumbs
of bread and survived.

00:20:33.260 --> 00:20:38.332
In Judaism, when the Gospel
describes Lazarus ending up in

00:20:38.332 --> 00:20:44.419
Abraham's bosom, it means... that
he ended up at the eternal feast.

00:20:44.419 --> 00:20:49.491
Everything he didn't receive on
earth, he received in heaven.

00:20:49.491 --> 00:20:56.592
And I return to the beginning of this
sermon, this sermon about the name.

00:20:56.592 --> 00:21:02.171
As soon as Jesus highlighted
Lazarus' name, it means He cares

00:21:02.171 --> 00:21:05.215
about the poor, those who suffer.

00:21:05.215 --> 00:21:13.838
So, I just want to tell you, be careful,
if you are suffering at this moment and

00:21:13.838 --> 00:21:22.461
if you don't have someone to feed you
crumbs of love, if you are weary in your

00:21:22.461 --> 00:21:30.576
soul, if you can't sleep, if something is
weighing you down and if no one notices

00:21:30.576 --> 00:21:33.620
your cry, remember, God sees everything.

00:21:34.820 --> 00:21:40.958
What matters to us is that eternal
reward, and it will not be missed.

00:21:40.958 --> 00:21:48.411
Because God is merciful, God is love, and
I believe that all of us who suffer or

00:21:48.411 --> 00:21:52.357
are in need will be with Him in eternity.

00:21:52.357 --> 00:21:57.180
May the Lord open our eyes
this Lent to notice, especially

00:21:57.180 --> 00:21:59.810
those who are close to us.

00:21:59.810 --> 00:22:04.195
Lazarus was close to this rich
man every day persistently.

00:22:04.895 --> 00:22:11.640
Let's open our eyes to those around us
who persistently beg for crumbs of love.

00:22:11.640 --> 00:22:12.090
Amen.

